The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Not ideal: Brendon
                                                   Not ideal: Brendon
                      
	The strong possibility of rain affecting the IPL was a big factor in the tournament not being shifted to England. The fact is that weather has become a huge player in South Africa!         
	Despite being a beneficiary, on Tuesday, the Kolkata Knight Riders captain, Brendon McCullum, said: Its not ideal... Its a shame to see such games decided by the Duckworth-Lewis Method...         
	The Kings XI Punjab have lost two matches on the D-L Method and the days second fixture at Kingsmead, the Mumbai Indians versus the Rajasthan Royals clash, was abandoned without a ball being bowled.                       OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT   IN DURBAN                                                                                                                    
